  A woman, whose name was not revealed, has been arrested for being in possession of human parts. According to spokesperson for Osun State Police Command, Folashade Odoro, the woman was apprehended at Centre Area, Ikire, Osun State, with a dried human hand in her possession. She explained that on a tip-off, the police intelligence unit accosted the suspect and she was found with the human part concealed in a bag. Odoro said that Commissioner of Police in the state, Johnson Kokumo, has directed a thorough investigation into the matter. She said the CP also warned that anyone caught dealing in human parts or committing any other kind of crime would be made to face the full wrath of the law.